data.content:
The fix is to **bypass `IFormFile`** entirely and read the multipart body section-by-section using `MultipartReader`, streaming each chunk straight to a `FileStream`.

**1. Disable buffering and raise limits** in `Program.cs`:

```csharp
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o =>
{
    o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024; // 2 GB
});

builder.Services.Configure<FormOptions>(o =>
{
    o.MultipartBodyLengthLimit = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024;
});
```

**2. Stream to disk** with `MultipartReader`:

```csharp
app.MapPost("/upload", async (HttpRequest request) =>
{
    // Verify content type
    if (!request.HasFormContentType ||
        !MediaTypeHeaderValue.TryParse(request.ContentType, out var mt) ||
        string.IsNullOrEmpty(mt.Boundary.Value))
    {
        return Results.BadRequest("Expected a multipart request.");
    }

    // Disable request buffering — critical for streaming
    request.EnableBuffering(bufferThreshold: 1024 * 64); // optional small memory threshold

    var boundary = HeaderUtilities.RemoveQuotes(mt.Boundary).Value!;
    var reader = new MultipartReader(boundary, request.Body);

    MultipartSection? section;
    while ((section = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync()) is not null)
    {
        if (!ContentDispositionHeaderValue.TryParse(
                section.ContentDisposition, out var cd) ||
            !cd.IsFileDisposition())
        {
            continue; // skip non-file fields
        }

        var trustedName = Path.GetRandomFileName();          // never trust the client name
        var savePath = Path.Combine("/tmp/uploads", trustedName);

        await using var targetStream = File.Create(savePath);
        await section.Body.CopyToAsync(targetStream);        // streams in chunks, ~80 KB default
    }

    return Results.Ok("Upload complete.");
})
.DisableAntiforgery();
```

**Why this works and `IFormFile` doesn't:**

| | `IFormFile` | `MultipartReader` |
|---|---|---|
| Buffering | Entire file into memory (or temp file after threshold) | Streams chunk-by-chunk (~80 KB) |
| Memory | O(file size) | O(constant) |
| 2 GB file | OOM / huge temp file | ~80 KB peak |

**Key gotchas:**
- **Don't bind `[FromForm]`** on the endpoint — that triggers the default form model binder which buffers everything.
- **`Path.GetRandomFileName()`** — never use the client-supplied filename for disk writes (path traversal risk).
- If behind **IIS/reverse proxy**, also raise its limits (`maxAllowedContentLength` in `web.config`, or nginx `client_max_body_size`).
